headline: KEYCORP LOWERS ITS PRIME LENDING RATE TO 6.75 PERCENT
summary: KeyCorp (NYSE: KEY) and its banking affiliates have lowered their prime lending rate to 6.75 percent from 7.00 percent, effective tomorrow, Dec. 11, 2025.

headline: JPMorgan Stock Slides on Warning of Steep 2026 Expense Growth
summary: JPM shares slide after the bank warns that 2026 expenses may surge more than $9B on growth spending, tech investments and inflation pressures.

headline: KeyCorp Stock Gains 3% on Record 2025 Revenue Growth Projection
